Date: Tue, 26 May 2015 10:49:52 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 087/452] staging: fsl-mc: Mark DPAA2 devices as coherent

We can use DMA ops specific to coherent devices, to a significant
performance increase from code like dma_map_sg().

NOTE: Current implementation is incomplete (default arguments only
working on kernels 3.19/4.0, but this may change with newer kernel
version).

Signed-off-by: Bogdan Hamciuc <bogdan.hamciuc@freescale.com>
Change-Id: Ie3552e6aed88ea02dddb24b09a78b624f9b615fe
Reviewed-on: http://git.am.freescale.net:8181/37680
Tested-by: Review Code-CDREVIEW <CDREVIEW@freescale.com>
Reviewed-by: Stuart Yoder <stuart.yoder@freescale.com>
[Xulin: Original patch taken from FSL LS2085 SDK EAR6.0,
LS2085A-SDK-SOURCE-20160304-yocto.iso]
Signed-off-by: Xulin Sun <xulin.sun@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/staging/fsl-mc/bus/mc-bus.c |    5 +++++
 1 files changed, 5 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/staging/fsl-mc/bus/mc-bus.c b/drivers/staging/fsl-mc/bus/mc-bus.c
index eb43013..f39cd42 100644
--- a/drivers/staging/fsl-mc/bus/mc-bus.c
+++ b/drivers/staging/fsl-mc/bus/mc-bus.c
@@ -536,6 +536,11 @@ int fsl_mc_device_add(struct dprc_obj_desc *obj_desc,
 			goto error_cleanup_dev;
 	}
 
+	/* DPAA2 devices on the mc-bus *are* dma-coherent.
+	 * FIXME: fill up @dma_base, @size, @iommu
+	 */
+	arch_setup_dma_ops(&mc_dev->dev, 0, 0, NULL, true);
+
 	/*
 	 * The device-specific probe callback will get invoked by device_add()
 	 */
